>>SOURCE FORMAT IS FREE

*> CalBot Blockchain Integrity Verifier Generator
*>
*> A COBOL program that generates a Kotlin source file containing
*> the blockchain chain verification logic for CalBot.
*>
*> This is COBOL acting as a transpiler: a language from 1959
*> emitting code for a language from 2011, which verifies a
*> blockchain whose genesis block hashes were also generated by
*> COBOL (see genesis_generator.cob).
*>
*> The generated Kotlin runs on all architectures (arm64, x86_64)
*> because it compiles to JVM bytecode.  The COBOL source is the
*> "enterprise specification" — the canonical definition of what
*> constitutes a valid blockchain for a calculator app.
*>
*> Build pipeline:
*>   COBOL (specification) -> gcobol (compiler) -> ELF (generator)
*>   -> Kotlin (emitted source) -> kotlinc (compiler) -> DEX (app)
*>
*> Compile: gcobol chain_verifier_generator.cob
*>              -o chain_verifier_generator
*> Run:     ./chain_verifier_generator > BlockchainVerifier.kt
*>
*> Language count update: COBOL is now responsible for TWO generated
*> Kotlin files in this project (GenesisBlocks.kt and this one).
*> The enterprise is expanding.

identification division.
program-id. chain-verifier-generator.

data division.
working-storage section.

*> Indentation control — Kotlin needs 4-space indents.
*> COBOL programs formatting whitespace-sensitive languages
*> is a special kind of irony.
01 ws-i1          pic x(4) value "    ".
01 ws-i2          pic x(8) value "        ".
01 ws-i3          pic x(12) value "            ".
01 ws-i4          pic x(16) value "                ".

procedure division.
    perform 100-emit-header
    perform 200-emit-verification-logic
    perform 300-emit-audit-formatter
    perform 400-emit-integrity-proof
    perform 500-emit-footer
    stop run.

*> ============================================================
*> Section 100: File header and class declaration
*> ============================================================
